<br>
For me, this would be a bad change.  Just my opinion.<br>
<br>
BTW, Prevent Flight is worth every point.  Not that I won't mind having the cost reduced.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(4/20/03 1:38:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dual Shadows</span><hr size=1> Kerrec, the point of the change is to make an anytime combo where you use Misty Gloom and then Dual Shadows. Misty Gloom is an anytime style that currently has horrible style bonus (less than Amethyst), yet has high endurance cost (Amethyst has medium end cost). <br>
<br>
Hopefully, the idea would be to up the style damage on Misty Gloom to make the anytime chain more effective. Otherwise, I'd recommend that Dual Shadows be left as a front positional with a better bleed effect and increased style damage.<br>
<br>
For the most part I really like the report. However, Anga, is it at all possible to change Dirty tricks to a PBAE effect? The simple reasoning is that this ability only affects 1 target and that target must be a melee character. TW and Frenzy have much more utility so I think making Dirty Tricks PBAE would be justified.<br>
<br>
Another issue that comes up in my mind is the notion that Mercs were intended to deal massive damage from their positional attacks (read in their character description). As such, I would actually prefer the Shadow's Edge-Penumbra style combo to remain the same, but have their damage increased and include a stun effect on Penumbra. I don't think a stun effect on the 2nd back-positional style is too much to ask when considering that Savages and LW users get a stun on their opening rear-positional styles.<br>
<br>
Kiamar Blackblade<br>
Mercenary Master<br>
Alerion Knight<br>
